      • unregister

        public VM.UnregisterInvocation unregister(java.lang.String vm)
        Description copied from interface: VM
        Removes the virtual machine corresponding to vm from the vCenter inventory without removing any of the virtual machine's files from storage. All high-level information stored with the management server (ESXi or vCenter) is removed, including information such as statistics, resource pool association, permissions, and alarms. This method was added in vSphere API 6.8.7.
        Specified by:
        unregister in interface VM
        Parameters:
        vm - Identifier of the virtual machine to be unregistered. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: VirtualMachine.
        Returns:
        instance of VM.UnregisterInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described unregister operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
